Patch Set 1:

Have you tried running these tests locally?  Reading through the bug, there was some suspicion that mox had something to do with the failure.  There was an effort to eliminate mox in favor of mock during Rocky, though not all use of mox was completely eradicated.  But maybe we got lucky here?

Patch Set 1:

I did, and unfortunately it tries to invoke the code that queries the image URL to get the image size. I spent a couple of hours trying to find a way to mock around it, but ended up with only a bad headache. Maybe if I could collaborate with someone with better mockery skills, we could figure something out....
